Business Talk with Michael Avery is South Africa’s leading online business talk show – and your company executives can take part in it. As part of the BusinessTech stable, Business Talk has excellent marketing solutions which allow executives to get featured on the show. This includes Executive Interview packages, offering unmatched exposure to a highly-influential business audience. All Business Talk interviews are published to the Business Talk website, BusinessTech, YouTube, Facebook, and Spotify – reaching an engaged audience. BusinessTech has been well received since launch, and reached 1.5 million views in February 2022. Business Talk sponsors have included Discovery Bank, EY, Discovery Business Insurance, EY-Parthenon, Sage, Microsoft, and Monocle – with the show hosted by highly-respected radio and TV personality Michael Avery. Avery is well known in business circles for his roles on Classic FM and Business Day TV – and as the anchor of the HOT Business show on HOT 1027. Guests on the show have included the biggest names in the South African business space, including Andrew Golding, chief executive of the Pam Golding Property group; Sim Tshabalala, joint chief executive of the Standard Bank Group; Magda Wierzycka, co-founder of Sygnia; and Michael Jordaan, co-founder of Bank Zero and founder of Montegray Capital. To find out more about Business Talk, contact BusinessTech’s marketing team.